==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: madrono
<hw>ma*dro"no</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>madro⟦ntil⟧o</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A small evergreen
tree or shrub (<spn>Arbutus Menziesii</spn>), of Pacific North America,
having a smooth bark, thick glossy leathery leaves, and edible
orange-red berries, which are often called <prod>madro⟦ntil⟧a
apples</prod>; the wood is used for furniture and the bark for
tanning.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>madro⟦ntil⟧o</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> madrona, manzanita, <spn>Arbutus
menziesii</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>madrilene</ent>⟦br⟧
